    "response_text": "The sequence begins with a static product-style shot on a bright yellow background. A box of **Glad ForceFlex** trash bags is shown, with visible packaging text including “GLAD,” “ForceFlex,” and “Tear Resistant / Less Plastic.” Below it appears the line: **“Small change. Big difference.”** The frame then cuts to black for several seconds.\n\nAfter the black screen, the setting changes completely. A cargo aircraft is seen flying high above clouds with its rear ramp open. The camera looks toward the open cargo bay from outside and then from inside. A person dressed in Western-style clothing, including a broad-brimmed hat, rides a black-and-white horned bull or steer out of the aircraft’s open rear ramp. The animal and rider drop into open sky.\n\nWide shots show the aircraft continuing in flight while the rider and animal fall away beneath it. Close-up and medium shots then show the rider airborne on the animal against a bright blue sky with clouds far below. The visuals are stylized and exaggerated: the rider appears to be “bull-riding” while falling through the sky.\n\nA close-up shows the rider’s torso and belt area. A yellow **Butterfinger** candy bar is visible tucked into a belt or holster-like pouch. The rider reaches down and pulls the bar out. Several close shots focus on his hand removing the yellow-wrapped bar while the sky and clouds remain in the background.\n\nThe rider, still airborne on the bull, holds up the candy bar. A close-up then shows him biting into the exposed chocolate end of the **Butterfinger** bar. His face is shown in profile and close-up as he eats it, wearing the dark cowboy-style hat and scarf. Another shot shows him holding the bar after taking a bite.\n\nThe scene returns to wide shots of the rider and bull floating or falling above the cloud layer. A second airborne person appears: a long-haired figure in light-colored clothing with a backpack or parachute-like gear is seen flying/falling through the sky toward the rider. In a later wide shot, this person approaches from the distance while the rider remains mounted on the bull and raises one arm.\n\nNear the end, the commercial cuts to a solid yellow screen with the large blue word **“BOLDER”** centered prominently. The final frame is an extreme close-up of a **Butterfinger** bar: the yellow wrapper with blue lettering is partly peeled back, exposing the chocolate-covered candy center."
